<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Single specimen (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 36" captionStartId="F36" captionText="Figure 36. Molpadiodemas stet. CCZ _ 194 A in situ image B tentacle ossicles C epibionts on ventral surface D detail of epibionts E dorsal surface F ventral view of specimen before preservation. Scale bars: 2 cm (A); 25 μm (B); 1 cm (E, F). Image attribution: Durden and Smith (A); Bribiesca-Contreras (B-D); Wiklund, Durden, Drennan, and McQuaid (E, F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.82172.figure36" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716362" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">36A</figureCitation>
). Colouration of live specimen is whitish yellow, with skin somewhat translucent (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 36" captionStartId="F36" captionText="Figure 36. Molpadiodemas stet. CCZ _ 194 A in situ image B tentacle ossicles C epibionts on ventral surface D detail of epibionts E dorsal surface F ventral view of specimen before preservation. Scale bars: 2 cm (A); 25 μm (B); 1 cm (E, F). Image attribution: Durden and Smith (A); Bribiesca-Contreras (B-D); Wiklund, Durden, Drennan, and McQuaid (E, F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.82172.figure36" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716362" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">36A, E</figureCitation>
). Body subcylindrical in live specimen, but dorso-ventrally flattened when preserved, tapering anteriorly, ~ 4 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide (L = 25 cm, W = 8.2 cm); semi-translucent body wall, longitudinal muscles visible through it; colouration of preserved specimen is yellowish (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 36" captionStartId="F36" captionText="Figure 36. Molpadiodemas stet. CCZ _ 194 A in situ image B tentacle ossicles C epibionts on ventral surface D detail of epibionts E dorsal surface F ventral view of specimen before preservation. Scale bars: 2 cm (A); 25 μm (B); 1 cm (E, F). Image attribution: Durden and Smith (A); Bribiesca-Contreras (B-D); Wiklund, Durden, Drennan, and McQuaid (E, F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.82172.figure36" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716362" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">36E</figureCitation>
), darker on the ventral side (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 36" captionStartId="F36" captionText="Figure 36. Molpadiodemas stet. CCZ _ 194 A in situ image B tentacle ossicles C epibionts on ventral surface D detail of epibionts E dorsal surface F ventral view of specimen before preservation. Scale bars: 2 cm (A); 25 μm (B); 1 cm (E, F). Image attribution: Durden and Smith (A); Bribiesca-Contreras (B-D); Wiklund, Durden, Drennan, and McQuaid (E, F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.82172.figure36" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716362" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">36F</figureCitation>
). Ventral surface with small, black, unidentified epibionts embedded in the skin (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 36" captionStartId="F36" captionText="Figure 36. Molpadiodemas stet. CCZ _ 194 A in situ image B tentacle ossicles C epibionts on ventral surface D detail of epibionts E dorsal surface F ventral view of specimen before preservation. Scale bars: 2 cm (A); 25 μm (B); 1 cm (E, F). Image attribution: Durden and Smith (A); Bribiesca-Contreras (B-D); Wiklund, Durden, Drennan, and McQuaid (E, F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.82172.figure36" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716362" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">36C, D</figureCitation>
). Specimen barely covered by sediment. Ossicles in tentacles; unbranched rods with thick central swelling; and branched rods, often with branches intertwining at the ends creating an irregular perforated mesh (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 36" captionStartId="F36" captionText="Figure 36. Molpadiodemas stet. CCZ _ 194 A in situ image B tentacle ossicles C epibionts on ventral surface D detail of epibionts E dorsal surface F ventral view of specimen before preservation. Scale bars: 2 cm (A); 25 μm (B); 1 cm (E, F). Image attribution: Durden and Smith (A); Bribiesca-Contreras (B-D); Wiklund, Durden, Drennan, and McQuaid (E, F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.82172.figure36" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716362" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">36B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
