</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</emphasis>
Single specimen; description of external morphological features only from in situ image as the specimen was damaged during collection (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 37" captionStartId="F37" captionText="Figure 37. Synallactidae stet. CCZ _ 061 A in situ image B tentacle ossicles. Scale bars: 2 cm (A); 50 μm (B). Image attribution: Durden and Smith (A); Bribiesca-Contreras (B)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.82172.figure37" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716363" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">37A</figureCitation>
). Body semi-circular, with ventral surface flattened, tapering distally; very wide, widest part of body ~ 7 cm; anus posterodorsal; mouth anteroventral. Tegument seems thick. Ossicles present in tentacles, slightly curved rods, &lt;250 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 37" captionStartId="F37" captionText="Figure 37. Synallactidae stet. CCZ _ 061 A in situ image B tentacle ossicles. Scale bars: 2 cm (A); 50 μm (B). Image attribution: Durden and Smith (A); Bribiesca-Contreras (B)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.82172.figure37" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716363" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">37B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
